title: Carey Mulligan talks baby daughter at 'Suffragette' premiere
text:
Updated: 10:31 p.m. Monday, Oct. 12, 2015 | Posted: 10:31 p.m. Monday, Oct. 12, 2015 Carey Mulligan talks baby daughter at 'Suffragette' premiere Related Writer Abi Morgan, from left, Helen Pankhurst, producer Alison Owen, Carey Mulligan, director Sarah Gavron and producer Faye Ward attend the premiere for "Suffragette" at the Paris Theatre on Monday, Oct. 12, 2015, in New York. (Photo by Evan Agostini/Invision/AP) Sponsored Links The Associated Press NEW YORK â€” 
Carey Mulligan gave birth a couple of weeks ago, but just recently revealed her baby's gender. 
It's Mumford and daughter for Mulligan and her husband. She's married to Mumford & Sons frontman Marcus Mumford. 
While on the red carpet Monday for her new film, "Suffragette," she says she had a little girl. 
The baby's name is Evelyn, Mulligan says smiling. 
The new mom says she has been too busy with the baby to process the experience. 
She says, "Ask me that in five years."
